  "prompt": "What are some of the biggest problems in Philippine public education?",
  "response": "Some of the biggest problems in Philippine public education include:\n\n1. Overcrowded classrooms\n- High student-to-teacher ratios\n- Limited physical space and resources\n\n2. Underfunded educational system\n- Low government spending on education\n- Insufficient infrastructure and learning materials\n\n3. Teacher quality and compensation\n- Low salaries for teachers\n- Limited professional development opportunities\n- Insufficient training and support\n\n4. Poor learning outcomes\n- Low national achievement test scores\n- High dropout rates\n- Limited access to quality education in rural areas\n\n5. Inadequate infrastructure\n- Lack of proper school facilities\n- Limited access to technology\n- Insufficient learning resources\n\n6. Curriculum challenges\n- Outdated curriculum\n- Mismatch between educational content and job market needs\n- Limited focus on critical thinking skills\n\n7. Language of instruction\n- Complexities with multilingual education\n- Challenges in transitioning between local languages and English\n\n8. Socioeconomic barriers\n- Poverty preventing school attendance\n- Child labor\n- Limited educational opportunities for marginalized communities\n\n9. Uneven educational quality\n- Significant disparities between urban and rural schools\n- Variations in educational standards across regions\n\n10. Bureaucratic inefficiencies\n- Slow implementation of educational reforms\n- Complex administrative processes\n\nThese issues collectively contribute to challenges in the Philippine public education system.",
